In this article, President Barack Obama declares September 14-20, 2014, as National Hispanic-Serving Institutions Week. The article emphasizes the importance of providing a world-class education for every child in America. It highlights the role of Hispanic-Serving Institutions (HSIs) in offering essential education opportunities to Hispanic students and increasing their college enrollment, retention, and graduation rates. The Federal Government is investing over $1 billion over 10 years in these schools to renew, reform, and expand higher education programs for Hispanics. The article also mentions the efforts made by the Obama Administration to increase college affordability and accessibility through initiatives such as Pell Grants, community college pathways, tuition tax credits, and better student loan repayment options. The proclamation recognizes the value of a college education in improving lives and revitalizing communities. It calls on public officials, educators, and all citizens to observe National Hispanic-Serving Institutions Week with appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities that acknowledge the contributions of these institutions and their graduates to the country.